article.headline: ETSU 93, Kennesaw State 62
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- Micah Williams scored 22 points and eclipsed the 1,000-point mark for his career in East Tennessee State's 93-62 win over Kennesaw State on Saturday. Williams, who was 9 of 17 from the field, including 4 of 8 from 3-point range, reached the milestone on a 3 with 17:55 to play. Mike Smith added a career-high 27 points, and Isiah Brown had 17 points and 12 rebounds for the Buccaneers (15-8, 10-2 Atlantic Sun Conference). Adam Sollazzo chipped in 15 points as ETSU won for the 11th time in 12 games. The Buccaneers led 55-29 at halftime after shooting 64.7 percent in the first half (22 of 34). They shot 62.3 percent for the game (38 of 61) and outrebounded the Owls 39-28. Kennesaw State (5-16, 3-8) was led by Markeith Cummings with 29 points. Spencer Dixon had 10 points for the Owls, who were held to just 4 of 17 from 3-point range (23.5 percent).
